Daniels Igoni, Yenagoa The All Progressives Congress in Bayelsa State has constituted a committee for the handover of government in the state on February 14. A statement on Wednesday by the state chairman, Mr Jothan Amos, said the committee would facilitate “the swearing in ceremony of the state governor-elect, Mr David Lyon, and the deputy governor-elect, Senator Biobarakuma Degi-Eremienyo.” The outgoing Governor Seriake Dickson of the Peoples Democratic Party would hand over to Lyon after completing his two terms of eight years approved by the constitution. According to the statement, a former Chief of Staff to former governor Timipre Sylva, Mr Samuel Ogbuku, is the chairman of the inauguration committee with Cynthia Princewill as vice chairman, while Mr Festus Daumiebi, will serve as secretary. It also listed eight sub-committee, including contact committee; venue and entertainment, protocol and transport committees. In all, the APC inauguration committee comprised 120 members. Copyright PUNCH.
